Python Data Types
│
├── Numeric
│   ├── int
│   ├── float
│   └── complex
│
├── Sequence
│   ├── str
│   ├── list
│   ├── tuple
│   └── range
│
├── Set
│   ├── set
│   └── frozenset
│
├── Mapping
│   └── dict
│
├── Boolean
│   └── bool
│
├── Binary
│   ├── bytes
│   ├── bytearray
│   └── memoryview
│
└── None
    └── NoneType

Numeric Data Types
------------------
-Used to store numbers.
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
int                   x = 10
float                 y = 3.14
complex               z = 2+3j

Sequence Data Types
-------------------
-Used to store collections of items
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
str (String)          name = "Akash"
list                  a = [1, 2, 3]
tuple                 b = (1, 2, 3)
range                 r = range(5)

Set Data Types
--------------
-Used to store unique elements.
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
set                   s = {1, 2, 3}
frozenset             fs = frozenset([1, 2, 3])  #output- frozenset({1, 2, 3})

Mapping Data Type
-----------------
-Stores data in key : value pairs.
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
dict                  d = {"id": 1, "name": "Ram"}

Boolean Data Type
------------------
-Used for True/False conditions.
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
bool                  x = True

Binary Data Types
-----------------
-Used for binary data.
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
bytes	                b = b"hello"
bytearray	            ba = bytearray(5) #output- bytearray(b'\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00')
memoryview	          mv = memoryview(b"hello") #output- <memory at 0x7ff1d6fe1d80>

None Type
---------
-Represents no value.
Data Type             Example
---------             -------
NoneType              x = None































